text:
Bohdan and his wife Victoria stayed with me for 5 nights. 
They came to my town for work so I didn't saw much from them, but the time we talked they've been really friendly, nice and a little bit shy. They've been always clean, quite and respectfull. 
I wish you guys good fortune for your business and much fun with you little doughter. I'll always have a open dor for you guys.

Bogdan and Veronika were rather optimistic about public transport in my area but they did make it before everything stopped.
Once they were here they were very involved in the dance festival here in Leverkusen for the first three days so I didn't see them very much.
But then they asked to stay longer and I agreed. So they finally stayed seven nights. In this period we had much more time together and I enjoyed having them around. On the practical side Bogdan helped me a bit in the garden and then cooked for all of us. That was nice. So I miss them now.

I hosted Orest for one day in  Warsaw. He seemed to be a really friendly, easy-talking to, kind person, thats why i highly recommend him as a good couchsurfer!! Have a nice trip to Germany and Czech republicüòÄ
Orest is a humble guy,I would recommend anyone to stay with him.

Orest is one of the best guys in Kyiv. Even he works a lot and we could not have time to hangout together, he did everything he can to help me. He also cooked me breakfast and a delicious dinner. He was normally going to host me for 2 days. My other host in the Kiev cancelled for the next 3 days but Orest was there to help me. He hosted me for 2 more days.He is an amazing person. You can trust him in anything.

Had a nice roof view, was interestinh to hear about his experience hitch hiking in Europe, very kind, will always take care if you are hungry and give directions or any other help, overall was great staying with him!:)

Hey there, I was 100/% recommend my little brother Orest, he is so friendly, open mind guy, working too hard as a Gym Couch, he cooked breakfast for us in the every early morning, like my mom‚Äôs do, hahahaha, big big hugs and thanks to Orest. Welcome to China! See you somewhere.

I had a blast staying with Orest. He's fun to hang out with, he knows the city, and he's a genuine and easygoing guy who knows the city in the way that only a native can.

His apartment is also really, really cool. An apartment with a rooftop ? Are you kidding me?

I only regret that I didn't have time to hang out with him more often, and get drunk with him on his rooftop due to his unusual work schedule.

Orest, my dude, thank you so much for opening your home to me and showing me your beautiful city. You're welcome in New Jersey any time, and the first round's definitely on me.

Being at Orest place immediately felt like home and he became like our friend instantly. We shared nice breakfasts, dinners and amazing drinks on his wonderful rooftop where you can relax and admire the lights in Kyiv. He also showed us his city by taking a long walk through peaceful parks and we had the time to share a lot about our hitchhiking experiences. I would recommend to everyone to go at Orest place in order to enjoy Kyiv from a roof and to learn more about Ukrainian Hitchhiking!! 
See you in France Orest and good trip to the Atlantic Ocean :)
fromPublicAddressDescription: La Baule-Escoublac, Pays de la Loire, France

text: Orest is great. His apartment is cosy and like described on a rooftop which is super cool, you have great views of Kiev out the window of his flat and a perfect spot on the roof to watch a sunset/sun rise. He has great stories about his road trip through Europe and his home has special touches like his hitchhiking signs and a flag with messages from his surfers(great idea). Thanks for having me Orest!

Sergiy is one of my best host during my CS experience. :) We had regular communication in advance via CS and WhatsApp. He gave me lots of valuable information in advance and professional description to find his apartment. Once i arrived he welcomed me with nice "brunch". He highlighted the main tourist attractions of the city and did the plan together what and how i should visit. :) Even i was busy with my MBA program in Kiev we always found time to have nice chat and food together. I loved the long night coversation about the local music, traditions, political situations. Do you know guys that Ella Fitzgerald: Summertime is from Ukraine? Sergiy has a cosy flat with brilliant view to the city from the 23rd floor. His cat, Sisha is just amazing! I liked playing with her very much! I prepared a "farewell" dinner of Hungarian "Paprik√°s Krumpli" for the last evening that was a perfect match with a local bottle of wine. Sergiy is very kind, easy-going, helpful and commited to feel yourself at home. He is very knowledgeable about the history, economic, political situation of Ukraine. :) I hihgly recommend to meet and stay with Sergiy. Thank you Sergiy again and very welcome anytime in Budapest!!! :)

Sergiy was a nice, hospitable, flexible and easygoing host. He had no problem with me staying one extra day and was very understanding when I suddenly had to leave for a couple of days during my stay. Sergiy is an open minded and knowledgeable person, which makes him a pleasant conversation partner. He likes to tell about what he knows, so I learnt a lot about Ukrainian history and politics from him. I really enjoyed his, Anna‚Äôs and their cat Chicha‚Äôs company as well as a relaxed creative ambiance at their place :)

It was really nice to meet Sergiy and his girlfriend Anna and stay at their flat with a lovely view of  Kiev for one day. They are very open and friendly people. They are travelling  a lot as well so we could exchange some experiences and thoughts about different parts of the world. Hope to see You next year guys:)

Sergiy was a great host. We had a lovely walk around the city the first evening we met.  He talked about the history of the country and the buildings we saw.  We eventually went home and talked about music and shared music files. The next day he went to visit his mother for the holidays and left me at the apartment to take care of his kitty.  It was a great place to stay, comfortable and close to the metro.  I was able to get into the center city quickly and explore the city.  I really enjoyed Kiev on my three day layover.  Thanks, Sergiy!

Was really a great experience to meet Sergiy, his girlfriend Anna and their joyful cat. Both me and my wife have spent 3 nights in their flat and it was really a great time for us, as both our hosts were very kind and helpful but also great companions for some interesting and long discussions, giving a good lesson about life in Ukraine, which I was particularly looking for. You simply cannot imagine nicer hosts while staying in –ö–∏—ó–≤. Too bad we did not have much time to visit the city together, however this was caused by our tight schedule so I am hoping to fix that in case they will visit us in Gda≈Ñsk, which by the way I would be looking forward to.
Sergiy's place was awesome. Greatest view of Kiev. He and his girldfriend were incredible hosts. They even open their doors at 6 A.M.!

Sergiy welcomed us in his place with a smile =) he knows a lotttt about history and can talk about it for many hours! Also he has great taste for music, is easy going and well traveled.

Pryvit Sergiy How are you

I and my GF felt comfortable staying at his place with the amazing city view. And they have a lovely trouble kitten that we had fun watching. 
I will never be tired of saying lots of thanks to Sergiy and Anna.  They made their best to help us. Sergiy kindly met me on his lunch break to put my huge backpack in his car so I could explore the city without my stuff weighing me down. He gave me a key and me free reign of his very lovely apartment offering lots of food.

The sofa and apartment is very comfortable and situated close to the metro so getting around is really easy. 

Thank you for hosting me and telling more about Ukraine!

While visiting Kiev in June 2017 Sergiy and his girlfriend Anna hosted me for a couple of nights. From the first moment I arrived, I felt like arriving to a home of an old friend - it's so funny to see how like-minded travellers around the world seem to be walking the same paths and visiting even the same shops :). 

During my stay Sergiy and Anna were taking good care of me and giving me a perfect introduction to Ukrainian culture and telling various interesting stories about Ukrainian history and explaining what's going on in Ukraine at the moment.

I would highly recommend to contact Sergiy for anyone interested getting a profound insight into Ukraine and spend some quality time sharing good stories and laughs.

Thanks once again for hosting and hope to see you soon again either in Ukraine or in Finland!

Henri

We had a nice time with his friends: visit a contemporary art museum, had delicious vegan food, walked around the nicest district of Kiev and beer hopping. I had a great time in his company. 

A single point is that my first night felt a bit strange because Stans didn‚Äôt show up until early morning. I would have appreciate if I could have been informed about that. 

I will never forget my time with Stans. I‚Äôm sure future surfer won‚Äôt either.

I just loved staying in Stanislav‚Äôs . He is very easy-going, kind and caring person. It was cool to chill with his friends. Also being in his flat is such good that it makes you don‚Äôt want to hang out at all:)

text:
Pavlo is the one who you can never get bored with.. He is very enjoyable, knowledgable, thoughtful and generous. First day he was busy and i tried to discover the city by myself. It was not fun and i could not see the city well enough. But day after he gave his whole day and night to me and he took me all around the city, introduced important history behind the buildings, took me very traditional and delicious restaurants/bars. I would never have seen even half of these places without his company. He made my Kyiv experience worthy and memorable. And... Ofcourse we joined wellknown Kyiv nightlife together. I have to confess that first day we went a place he likes and i loved the night. Second day we went several famous clubs which i forced him to go. But i did not like much.. So please trust his suggestions and never force him to go somewhere he does not like! =)
Btw, his home is well located, clean and confortable. I felt like my home..
My dear friend, thanks again for your great hospitability. I am happy that i have a new good friend in Kyiv! Looking forward to continuing in Bursa soon..

Hugs,
Sinem

It's been a very pleasant stay with Pavlo, even though it was a short time but we managed to hang out and had lots of interesting conversations. He's a very knowledgeable and easygoing person and can discuss many topics especially music or any artistic things! Really grateful that he took me around many places in the city, a perfect introduction to Ukraine and he's the perfect company to be around! Regret to go to Hungary too soon...missing Ukraine already!
Pavlo is a great guy. We have the same crazy humor and we laughed a lot. I love this guy and now is not just a host but a friend.

Pavlo hosted us for 2 nights in his central, historic apartment. He took us for picnics, the special kind of picnic in the not so easy to find spots in Kiev. 
He also taught us how to make Borsch the way his Grandma does. When the beetroot turns a lighter colour, the onion is golden, don‚Äôt forget the beans, and once it becomes Cinderella it‚Äôs ready :-D! 
Pavlo, was kind and lived simply, his liking of plants and Ukraine‚Äôs history was very interesting. 
Until next time! All the best man!

During my trip to Ukraine Pavlo was my host and knowledgeable guide in Kyiv. He devoted his time to show me some ‚Äòmust sees‚Äô and ‚Äòonly locals know‚Äô places that was a big advantage as I did not research much about the city before visiting it. I was also lucky to meet a few of his friends, who were very interesting and cool people!

Being easy going and intelligent man Pavlo made me feel relaxed, comfortable and welcomed. Right after first meeting I could feel that I have a friend in Ukraine with whom was easy to discuss any topic over meal or drink, joke and simply be honest while sharing my views. Thanks to Pavlo and his friends I know how cool and hospitable Ukrainians are! I hope to meet Pavlo on other occasion and share some good moments again!

Pavlo was a very good, kind and understanding host. He is very generouse and a good listener. His home is clean and centraly located. Very good experience staying with Pavlo. Thank you again for letting me stay with you, Pavlo.

Pavlo is a good guy, I apologize for not being present more of the time. But then after a day, we finally got to connect and laugh, and it was a lot of fun. So thank you for being so nice to host us and showing us amazing content. Wishing you the best and I‚Äôm excited to hang out again soon

Pavlo is such a great person. It was my first couch surfing experience and it was awesome! We went for night walkings and pub crowling!!! (That was enjoyable!) and we went The Night Museum (Golden Gates actually but being in a museum in the night is first for both of us) I won't forget about this trip, thanks for everything Pavlo!!

Pavlo = legend.

Ok so Kiev is a great city but Pavlo really made my stay memorable and awesome. He's one of the most knowledgable and interesting people you'll meet - telling you everything you need to know about history, culture, sights, hidden gems and a really good understanding of Ukraine.

He introduced me to new bands, films, fun facts and also took time to hang out in the evening. He knows how to make a new city comfortable but really fun. I had a great time staying with Pavlo.

First, I would like to say a big THANK YOU for hosting me! I was lucky to be hosted by Pavlo. You really cannot wish anything more: nice flat in the city centre, an amazing weather, and surely great host Pavlo!  He is not just hospitable, reliable, friendly and caring person, but also intelligent, funny and cheerful guy! I was covered with his attention and care all four days of my stay. 
He perfectly organized my luggage storage in the first evening, when I arrived, because he couldn‚Äôt meet me, because of his studies.
 The 2nd day he took me to the Flower Walk (Hana Sampo) in the Botanical Garden; such a beauty of so many blossoming lilacs in one place, I have never seen before, and enjoyed it a lot! 
He gave me good tips and recommendations, what I can see by my own, when he is at work.
But most I liked our evenings/nights with long conversations!  We could find so many topics and things in common to talk to, tasting nice Ukrainian beer and wine, and without realising how much time have passed ))
I highly recommend Pavlo as a host and as a guest!  If you have a chance to meet him, to be hosted by him or to host him in your place, don‚Äôt miss it ;))
Take care, Pavlo, and I hope to see you once again in Lithuania!

3 nights in the centre of Kiev with Pavlo, what a pleasure for Manuel and me! He challenged our minds and ideas, made us taste and cook delicious food, took us on long walks through the city, shared ukrainian beer with us & showed us crazy good films! A clever, kind, fun, inspiring guy definitely worth spending time with! Enjoy!!
Very great guy. Helped me with everthing because I didn‚Äôt speak the language. Have me great directions for going everywhere and to get to him.

Pavlo hosted me and my boyfriend fir two days in Kiev. It was a great experience because he hanged out with us and also show around the city. We enjoyed conversation and it was interesting to talk to a person who took part in Maidan revolution. Hopefullt we meet again and you are welcome to come to Lithuania! He was my best host on my travel. It was comfortable night in his place. I enjoyed my day with him. He is funny and love to share what he has, what he knows. Even he will teach you something new. Excellent man! Paul is always ready to communicate! And it is always with fun! Paul can talk about serious things with humour))) 
He already lived half the year in Thailand and told a lot about the Thai lifestyle.

Absolutely great time with Pavlo in Ubon! He was working  during days, but he gave a lot of good advices and directions on Ubon. text:
I stayed with Paul and Marian in there apartment in Kiev. Paul was very patient and waited an hour and a half for dumb american (me) to navigate through absurd, Ukrainian alphabet.

He showed me around the city, bar hopping and he knew A LOT of knowledge about the city. Make sure you take notes while you walk around because he does quiz you. You get extra bonus points for writing in a Moleskine. 

We went to an opera, it was supposed to be comedy. I think it was, the jokes were in Ukranian, his very nice girlfriend explained the story to me.

If I were you, and in Kiev I would "hit up" Paul and see if he's "down" to "hang" or get a beer. I don't think he likes to "cut rug" though

text:
My time spent in Kiev was amazing and all thanks to Maksim. I felt really good in his place and his company. He showed me around some pretty awesome places, brought me to amazing party and he even showed me how extreme I could be! :) 
His home is just  perfection and he is a very easy going person. Perfect holidays in Kiev! I didn't want to leaveeee... 
Well, thanks again my friend, and hope to see you some day somewhere :)

Maksim is a very nice guy, respectful, and I had a good stay at his place.
He is funny, active and friendly. He took me around town, helped me with my computer and also with my questions about the city.
My room was super comfortable and big! The unit is not far from the city center, accessible via metro!
I would totally stay with Maksim again and hopefully I get to host him one day.
Tks Maksim!!!!!

Maksim hosted me for 3 nights in Kiev. He had been super friendly and helpful during my entire stay. 
Unfortunately he was super occupied with work, working late, so we mainly met in the mornings. Despite work stress, one evening he showed me some non touristic views on Kiev. 
He is a super talkative and open minded guy that traveled quite a lot. He was easy to talk to with good attitude. 
His place is very comfortable, I had a good sleep and could spent as much time there as I wanted. 
Overall a very good experience. I highly recommend Maksim as a couch surfer and hope to meet again. Thank you so much and all the best.

Maksim is just the best guy! Whenever we are in Kiev we reach out because we are lucky to call him a friend.

text: I'm really glad I was able to stay with Ihor in Kiev! He was kind enough to host me for 4 nights - I was there during the work week, but joined him for his salsa classes every evening, as well as an open air salsa event and a couple of evening hangs with his lovely friends. I am in love with salsa and dancing, so being invited to dance every night was a perfect welcome for me :D I found Ihor to be refreshingly straightforward, honest, humble, trusting, friendly and curious about life, and we had a number of good chats (and eats! :P). He's super chill and I'd be happy to stay with him again, or to meet up in California or elsewhere around the planet! Thanks again so much for your hospitality and I wish you so much fun on the dance floor! :)

I first met with Ihor at the Metro station where he showed me the way to his clean, well located apartment. He has some awesome decorations inside with plenty of stories tied into his well thought out interior.  
I then went out alone and explored the city. Somehow Ihor convinced me to meet him at a dance studio and attempt dancing. I mostly managed to embarrass myself, but everyone there was very supportive and I thoroughly enjoyed laughing at my own clumsy footwork. 
The following day I went on a walking tour in the afternoon. Later I met Ihor at a really amazing outdoor gym. This place is 10 x better than muscle beach! A lot of interesting equipment, and people.
Later that night Ihor had some friends over at his place. We all got along really well. We drank, ate food, talked,  and of course listened to gangster rap music. One of his friend's even offered me a ride to Odessa the following morning!
I look forward to hosting him in the USA!

Having Andrew and his friend around  is absolutly great. Both are so kind, friendly and easy going. It has been  a pleasure right from the start. Andrew is an awesome guy and we had a great time together. He showed me some cool places, cooked traditional food for me and we talked about our adventures around the world. Thank you so much for everything, I highly appreciate it!!!

Andrew was a really cool host, who  show us many really beautiful places in Kiev and took us to great restaurants serving ukrainian food and to a cool pub.

I reccomend Andrew to all couchsurfers!

Spending New Years Eve with Andrew, Vitja (and of course Marta!) was highlight of our trip to Kyev. When I planned this trip, I was quite nervous if someone will take us during this holiday. In the end, it was really great. Our hosts prepared great food and drinks as well, including home-made horilka. But even more enjoybale than food were conversations about many things, travelling, comparing our Czech and Ukrainan language and culture. Their flat is small but very cosy and comfortable. Next day we spent time together walking in the centre of Kyjev. Although we spent there only one night in the end, it seems as much more! Thanks a lot for a wonderful experience!

Andrey, the hospitable owner of a neat apartment in walking distance from the station. Kindly offered to meet us off the road. We rested from the bus, discussed common interests. Andrei is an enthusiastic tourist and sportsman. With the fact that he himself lives in Kiev for a couple of years, he knows the city very well! He knows many interesting facts about the city and is well-oriented.

Andrey accepted my urgent CS-request although he already hosted his friend. It requires to be enough flexible and open-minded to make such decisions. Also Andrey is sociable, hospitable and interesting to talk to. I felt like home.. very comfortable. I didn't use CS for pretty long time and it was a pleasure to get into the friendly atmosphere with people whom you didn't know just some hours ago.

We'll be glad to see again guys!
And good luck with CS-experience!

Very communicative and interested in a lot of things Vira and Sasha were great guest. I really enjoyed their company plus have seen some part of Berlin I wanted to visit for quite some time. Though I couldn't spend too much time with them, the time I did spend with Vira and Sacha was good.

I have the pleasure to host this really friendly couple. Unfortunatly I didn t have so much time to share with them but a nice talk before to sleep and at the breakfast. Fun and friendly couple. They were very respectful and even did the dishes without me asking

Vira + boyfriend booked to stay with me but things changed but (a second but) they came to oostende and I did a tour for them, I wish I was a bit more motivated, and next time I see them I hope I am full of more energy, they liked my cat and Princess Meow Meow loved them, till next time!!

Vira and Sasha are very,very friendly couple. They are very polite, intelligent, positive and easy goin. From the first moment when I met them we could not stop the chat (and I was so hungry.. haha). Vira and Sasha were fantastic guests - well-mannered, friendly, knowledgeable, open-minded, curious about the world and other people,  they complement each other which makes them a good speaker and listener. Staying with Vira and Sasha was great. They are very friendly and open minded. They loved to show us Kiev. They are very hospitable and are a great first stop when visiting Ukraine. Kiev was a wonderful experience. Vira and Sasha were so helpful to receive us. We meet with Sasha and he take us out to known so many beautiful places finishing with a great funicular trip.

Next day they show us where was the better places to continue our Kiev discovery. At night we dinner together and they help us with anything, even curiosities about our country. Their house is amazing, clean, neat and full of affection to receive tried travelers.
We have no way to thank you, just wish that you travel to Colombia to share again a time with both of you.

Thanks!
Lauanda e Andr√©s

Beside a clean- comfortable house, punctuality, humour, welcoming nature;  the quality that I admire from the depths of my heart was their constant concern and care about me. I had wished for visiting Odesa next and they helped me in arranging my trip to every extent. Not just that,  Vira made sure that I reached Odesa safe and sound. I feel very apologetic for the inconvenience she went through because of that,  and at the same time extremely grateful. In short, her concern reminded of my sister. ‚ù§ 
And about Sasha, he was working from early morning till evening, but he walked with me for around 5 hours and showed me places which I couldn't have discovered myself. He is the best ever Guide for Kiev!! 
I really wish that our paths cross again.  I would love to have them at my house back in Pakistan.

I‚Äôm so happy that I had the opportunity to meet Vira and her boyfriend. They are very friendly and easy to talk to. They were both extremely helpful and showed me how to navigate my way around the city. When Sasha finished work he showed me around his favorite parts of Kiev. Thank you so much for hosting me, I had a wonderful time!

Vira and Sasha are super nice and friendly people. It was nice to stay with them, even if we had not that much time to hang out  since they had to work and we were busy too. But the few hours spent together were very interesting and nice

It was lovely to meet both Vira and Sasha, who are a lovely couple living together ~1 hr away from the city center. It was easy to get to their place, supported by meeting Vira at the metro each night, and Sasha taking us to the city in the morning. We had a short but lovely time discussing different topics together and eating homemade Varenyky. We wanted to learn about Ukrainian culture and lifestyle, so it was perfect to hear about their passion for their country. Please continue being wonderful and open. Thank you and hope to see you in Bavaria!!

It was wonderful to stay with them! I first came too late but Sascha waited for me, showed me around in Kiev and helped me alot with my further travels. Really helpful and thoughtful! We had a tipycal ukrainian soup, i could take a shower and had a safe and sound sleep!

Would love to jost you two one day in Germany! Take good care,
Heidi

I stay 2 nights Sasha&Vera s apartment .  Especially thank you Sasha that he take me from the metro station first day to the their  apartment . They have had good traditional Ukrainian foods . Thank you for hosting me .
Vira and Sasha a great couple that was really hospitable and friendly, with nice apartment not far from metro, was nice to talk with them and stay at their home ;)

Sasha and Vera are sociable, friendly and cheerful. They are interested in both hiking and cultural trips abroad. We met with the guys in the subway and went home together to the suburbs. The sleeping place is cozy, the apartment is clean. We stayed two nights, talked on different topics: from travel to a healthy diet. We will be glad to visit them again.

Vira and Sacha have been prevent with me, they have explained me very well how to go through the city. In add they have
accepted to spend time a little bit afterwork and i think it was not easy for them because it was a week who they have had a lot of work. I was lucky they cooked holubtsi for me, special ukrainian meal ! I'm very grateful. They're good persons in an outsanding city.
Vira and Sasha were great hosts!! They showed me around the city, they answered all my questions, they were really friendly and helpful :D

It was really great and memorable stay in Kiev! Vira was traveling at that time, but her boyfriend Sasha hosted me  and, despite he was very busy, he found time to show me so many things and places in Kiev that I really started to feel like at home there :D  
He is very friendly, interesting and positive person, who also taught me how to make a delicious breakfast with cous cous and eggs! Thank you for everything and wish you two good luck with traveling to Brussels, and hope to see Sasha again and meet Vira in person next time :)

We still can't believe how lucky we were to find such nice and hospitable people! Thank you so much for understanding, coziness and safety. Thank you, Vira, for readiness to help, excellent sense of humour and a whole exhibition of shower gels:) Sasha, thank you for a wonderful breakfast and for detailed instructions on how to spend another day in Kyiv (btw, we haven't visited museums, sorry). Thank you, guys, you've made our trip way more pleasant and unforgettable! I hope you'll always be fine, wish you to have a great time this summer and remember, we always wait for you in the Carpathians üòä

It was an awesome experience to be hosted by Vira and Sasha. They were so nice, caring, friendly, knowledgeable,  always ready to advise. Vira came to the station for us at 11 pm and was waiting one hour because our train was late.  Vira and Sasha are fantastic guides, they spent with us all two days showing us the city, sharing knowledge, telling stories,  introducing their friends. It was an incredible, unforgettable weekend. Couchsurfing let us meet them in January and I hope it's just the beginning of our mutual visits.

Vira and Sasha was super griendly and thoughful. Vira made a very good explanation of the places and I had no difficulties when I am in Kiev. I stayed in Sasha and Vira's cozy apartment for two nights. Thank you for their immediate response. text:
Vira and Sasha hosted me for 4 nights in Kiev. This was not just about a simple host. I've got a full service. 
They (+ theri friend Dima) are extremely friendly and hospitalable. I was treated like their best friend from the first moment when Sasha was waiting for my shuttle bus in the city center.
They showed me the sightseeings of the city, good restaurats, bars and coffee houses + "marsrootka" = local public transport mini buses. They made my trip to Kiev unforgetable.
Thank you, guys. CU next time.

Vira and Sasha have helped us really much to get familiar with the town! Their hospitality was really warm, and they have the great quality to make feel the people at ease at their home. They gave us usefull tips about what was worthy to visit in Kyiv, and to move and where to find up the most interesting spots. Sasha was an excellent tourist guide, devoting his time to show us all the best that the awesome Kyiv can offer (including the restaurant Garbuzik, with its delicacies). Thanks a lot to Vira for have cooked really delicious dishes (the vegetarian borshch was super tasty) and for have shared with us funny jokes and interesting stories.

Sasha and Vira are both very nice people,  they are clean and helpful. Vira loves cats :D Me and my boyfriend stayed for three nights, Sasha was taking care of us because Vira was away.  He was very kind, he took us to the city and together with his friend we were walking through the not-yet-explored parts of Kiev :) We also tasted typical food and discovered a lot about economy or history...Vira arrived the last day and seemed as a very cheerful person. She also helped us to get a taxi to the airport in the morning. I would definitely recommend this couple!

Vira and Sascha are really great hosts and i can definitely recommend to stay with them! They are friendly and open minded and you can have really nice talkes with them. 
They live in the suburbs quite in the near of kiev but they took me every morning to the city center and picked me up every evening. They also made super delicious varenyky!! And on my first day I also got a really nice city tour in the evening. 
So, if you want to have great experiences in kiev stay with vira! :)

For three days I live in Vira's house. Unfortunately I couldn't meet Vira personally, however I spend this time with her boyfriend - Sasha. That was really nice time. Shasha hosted me and my friend and shown us the best places in the city.
Thanks you Sasha!

Thanks to Vera for response and Alexander's hospitality. We with wife stayed for two nights in their apartment. Alexander has meet us and showed where he lives. Also he advised interesting places for us. We were feeling very comfortable and cosy. Either, he is a good conversationalist, I found common topics with him and we were talking till night. We were happy to visit you, thanks.

Me and my boyfriend Pawe≈Ç staied at Vira‚Äôs place  for one night and I really regret that it was only one. Vira is talkative, friendly and easy going person like her boyfriend Sasha. They spent with us time, showed city and Ukrainian restaurants. They told us a lot about Ukrainian traditions, current situation and history. I truly recommend them!

Vira and Sa≈°a saved me and my girlfriend so much. After having some very unpleasant experiences with hostels in Kiev they openly and quickly accepted our request to stay with them. "In hard times you get to know your friends" says a saying in my country and I'll never forget how they helped us when we really needed it. 
They are both kind and hospitable. They love to share their experiences and are very interested in hearing yours.
I hope we meet again oneday and I wish them all the best :), H&M
Vira and Sasha and all their friends are an awesome company and hosts, highly recommended!:)

Dear Sasha and Lera I can't stop thinking how pity it was not to have more time with you guys. I conctacted them when I was in a really busy moment and I'm ashamed to say it was the first time I could't join out with couchsurfers and it really was a shame....  What a nice couple, seriously.  I was having difficult days, long working hours and when I got home I found the meal prepared, both days... how awesome is that hahaha. Thanks a lot. Thanks a lot for the history lesson, Sasha knows quite about history and he shared it with me, and I know he knows lot more. If I have to use one word  is humbleness, in the best sense you can get. You were so thoughtful all the time, and you can notice clearly its not because I was hosting you, you are truly like that. It makes me love humanity more and more when I witness people like you are real hahah.  But I dont have to use one word so, I wanted to say to you I really admire how flexible you are, and also that you are a clever couple that dont hesitate in using best qualities of each other and is amazing to see how you work as a team. I'm very happy for you guys. And I love people that are clear, that are not afraid to share, I wish i could meet you again in better conditions so I'm not just a spirit walkingaround the house. Thanks again for coming here, you cheered my days up with your deatils and the way you made me feel confortable while we knew each other a little. All the best, great Sasha and Lera i really mean it. :D

Unfortunately I just stay one night at his place, but we were able to share nice conversation, a phone call and many stickers in Telegram :) But Alex summed it up perfectly: there are so much things to do before we die. Alex, I really hope we find the time for a next exchange, here in Berlin or in Kiev. You are always welcome for sure! I hope your driving exam went well and that you achieve all your other goals! text:
HeyHey Mister AllatRa! :P
How are you?

Well, I spent 4 days with Alex in Kiev and I truly had a great time! We shared some tasty tee, some good veggie food and a moment of meditation in Lavra! Well, in my case I just tried...:-)
Alex gave me a different point of view about the revolution in Ukraine, and was really interesting to listen to his stories about life, hicthhiking, and yeah...he also told me two or three things about signs and symbols around us :D

I like CS because it gives you the chance to meet people with the same "hobbies" but also that could open you a new world! That was my experience with Alex, and now I have a mission to do...:-)

Alex, I hope to meet you again somewhere (not in Switzerland, right?) and I wish you all the best!
Take care
jack

text:
Well... somehow it happened that I made last minute decision to visit Bykhov, small mysterious town with hidden stories from the past. And I will never regret for that decision as I got the chance to meet one of the most interesting characters in this country! Sasha is very intelligent, deep and good person who is able to find hidden meaning in every action, and sometimes explain unexplainable things :) 
That evening when I came to Bykhov with Solenne and Nadja, left strong impression on me, thanks to Sasha. His stories about every corner of that town made that place unique, and added special energy to the town. Long walk on the winter night, then standing on the bridge over Dnepar on midnight and the first snow on the train station created an evening hard to forget. Next day we explored history of the town and shared our stories with local newspaper :) That evening we met again in Rogachov and I am sure we will meet again somewhere on this planet!

Marianna was friendly, helpful, and responsive from Day 1: she sent me a lot of super detailed info about where to meet and how to get there, and she knows literally everything about the public transport in Kiev, as well as the history of many of the establishments. She and her wonderful friend took me to rooftops to see the sunrise and gave me an absolutely adventurous and crazy 15h layover experience.

text:
It was a real privilege to stay with Tetiana and her husband Anatoly. They were wonderful company and so very welcoming. They were a reminder of what couchsurfing is all about and I thank them for educating me about their country and for giving me such an enjoyable stay. It was lovely that Tetiana cooked typically Ukrainian food for lunch i.e. borsch (aka borscht) followed by stuffed peppers. I really enjoyed that experience! 
I hope one day that they will stay with me in the UK so that I can return the favour and take them for a walk in the woods too.
My stay was made very special by two very kind and interesting people. And it was an extra bonus meeting their daughter and her boyfriend. What more can I say? A real joy!

Tetiana and Anatoriy are both very kind, well-read, cultured, organised, elegant, hospitable, caring and friendly. They take great interest in their guests and their cultures, as well as they are always willing and happy to share their  experience of travels, thoughts and experienced in general. They are both enthusiastic, adventurous, vital, always up for leaning new and good things, young at heart whilst they also offered me deep, intellectual and meaningful conversations. Anatoriy has a great sense of humour and Tetiana is a versatile smart beautiful lady that has great organisation skills at home and work, her culinary and photography skills are remarkable that she generously shared with me. Every day we had long and  interesting conversations over a meal, tea and walk in their neighbour woods. We cooked together, cleaned together  exchanged our respective home recipes. I will try to make at home. They seem to enjoy the wine, different sweets from different countries and Japanese handicraft I brought, if you seek hint for your eventual gifts for them I think a bottle of good red wine or/and some beautiful  souvenir along with your travel stories would be a great idea. :) thank you so much again for your hospitality, I hope to repay your kindness in near future. Please drop me a message if you ever visit Japan or any of countries I know well. I am here to help:-) All the best

I felt extremely lucky and grateful to be Tetiana's first guest. Tetiana and her husband Anatolii were very kind to me. I ended up arriving in Kiev a few days later than I originally planned, Tetiana was very understanding about my change of plans. As soon as I arrived I could tell that I liked both of them, they greeted me with warm smiles. Tetiana made me fall in love with  a few different kinds of foods, I only hope that I can make them again and they will be half as tasty as when she made them.  I had a very nice hike with Anatolii, and I was happy to see some beautiful nature as well as small village and talk with him. I also had a really great talk through the city with Tetiana, I feel I got to see a lot more with her than I would have on my own :) So it was very nice to get to spend time with both of them! As well as meeting their daughter ( who is as nice and as smart as they are!) and her boyfriend. I felt very comfortable during my time there, and they were always wanting to help me or make my stay better. I really appreciate their kindness and I feel humbled to meet such nice people. Tetiana also gave men one reading suggestions which I am looking forward to trying :)  Tetiana was a truly wonderful host, which makes sense because she is a wonderful person! If you are looking to host. her, or stay with her, I give her my highest recommendation!

Wow!!! I really enjoyed the time spent with my new friend Peter. He's a very unusual guy. Me and two my two friends were lucky to stay at Yevgeny's place in Kiev. He rents Ukrainian style three rooms apartments with five residents not far from city center, close to the supermarket and metro station. Yevgeny is really nice, attentive, interesting, bright and frank person. It was very nice to hear stories about Kiev, Ukraine and other places. 

Thanks and all the best!

text: Wow... Dan&Nat..how to describe my weekend stay at your place? You both are full of kindness, help, communication and relaxing. Everything i need to feel comfotable. You, your friends, your house and even your dogs made Me feelling like home. Keep going for it and just go with the flow :-) thanks for everything and i can stay that i have friends in Kiew now. I really hope to see you soon. All the best for you two and thanks again!!!

Dennis and Nat are a very creative couple with a great taste of things! They both are truly talented and you can feel that staying at their super decorated apartment and listening their stories of learning things. 
They are extremely friendly and they are happy to introduce their 1 million friends to you, play board games and spend time on the rooftop together :) The thing I was personally very grateful for, they showed me a series of short documentary movies of their friends about underground activities around Ukraine, which I enjoyed a lot. The sleepless nights will stay in my memory, guys!:) they navigated me around, where I could eat and how I could reach places I needed. Oh, and I didn't mention their lovely dogs and a cat! 
well, it was definitely a fun time, I wish I was less exhausted after all my journeys to be much more involved in your parties, guys! Thank you for everything!

Dennis and his girlfriend Nat were such amazing hosts! They have a very spacious cozy apartment equipped with a large comfortable couch and many forms of entertainment. They took me on a pleasant tour around town and gave me many recommendations on places to visit. In the evening, we were able to connect over some beers and tea, and I'm glad we were able to share our stories and learn from each other. I'm truly grateful to have met Dennis and Nat and for the kindness and hospitality they provided. If you ever get a chance to stay with or host Dennis and Nat, don't hesitate to do so!

Dennis and Nat, it was truly a pleasure getting to know you and thank you so much for everything. Best of luck on everything and I hope to see you guys again somewhere soon on this wondrous Earth! :)
Great guys!!! Great digs!!! Friendly, funny, clear, creative! SO so so good!

That was a super positive CS experience! Definitely! Firstly Dennis welcomed me at his huge appartment with a girlfriend, many friends, 2 dogs and a cat and the first half of the evening we spent in their kitchen and another one - on the balcony laughing about plenty of funny jokes. So many things were done like playing cards, drinking beer, telling tons of funny stories and walking to some local bar. I haven't even thought that I can do so many different things for so short time:) Den and Natasha is very polite and easy-going couple, it seemed to me that they are my old friends!:) Don't hesitate any second to host or stay with these awesome guys! Hope to see you one day in Poltava, you are more than welcome there!:)

It was an awesome experience staying with this guy in Kyiv. He met me as I arrived at the metro station near his home. Him and his girlfriend, dogs, and cat were definitely cool company. They have a beautiful home with an an amazing rooftop view of the city. I had told Dennis that I had already seen most of the touristy stuff of the city and that I had wanted to see more places not all the tourists see, and he took me on walk around to more local places he visits. I was able to try some nice local beers every night too. It was nice meeting his friends too and just hanging out, playing Nintendo, doing a barbecue, having a cup of coffee and chatting. This is the reason I CouchSurf... to get to know the local culture and see what people do to enjoy themselves in their own environment. I enjoyed every moment and hope I can one day return the favor. Thanks again for your hospitality! Mahalo!
Nice and fun person! Unfortunately I didn't have a chance to hangout a lot with Katya as was busy at work, but overall great experience! 100% recommend

Mitya and Lilia stayed at my place for two nights. They were the first couch surfers I was hosting and I had a blast. Mitya is an amazing person, super fun, intelligent and humble. My house will always be open for him (and Lilia). :)

Mitya is very funny, polite and easy to get along. Although I didn't had much to go around with him, I enjoyed the few moments we spent together talking and sharing a beer.

Alyona was a wonderful host. Thoughtful and friendly. She gave me everything I needed for the stay (e.g. towels, pj) and treated me with delicious food. But above this all, she is a wonderful person to talk to, damn smart and profound!

Thank you much Julia for showing me your house your life and your stuff... Good luck and you have a friend in Madrid right now... Cheers ; )

I stayed two nights with Julia‚Äôs family. They are all positive, Alex and 3 children. I had really nice experience with an precious Ukrainian family. Julia is doing everything for making your staying comfortable. She sings Ukrainian traditional songs with nice voice and her lovely 2 year old daughter Magdalena dancing! What a nice picture! We walked around national forest close to her house and had a picnic accompanied with the bird songs) and she introduced me with her mother as well, so all my feelings on this staying was excellent. Thank you all lovely family)
Nice lady and very friendly person
I loved staying and feeling at home. Thank you!

Julia is someone who has developed herself and transfers it to her children as it is.Julia was the be answer for me that question; "a mother can be both determined and loving".I've never seen a mother so successful in my life. The princess of 1.5 years old, eating Magdalena's food with her own hands,the 9-year-old intelligence cube,Kyril's own washing his own clothes,Daniel's egg baking at 7 years old,Julia's success.
Julia also sang songs with a community trying to keep the traditional ukraine songs to be forgotten.When the queen bee started singing,it was great to see the lovely little bees around him accompany her.
Julia's house is very close to the protected national park.We had long walks together,felt the trees,talked with the birds.She introduced her parents and sisters,very lovely warm people.His wife Alex is very responsible, very kind.he got up early and brought me to the terminal by car.
It is a great gift for me to recognize these people.I will miss so much

After a really well described & welcoming invitation, I was welcomed by the whole family after arriving to the bus stop. During the night the filled my belly and together with the whole family and friends they warned my heart. 

Especially being around her so open and interesting kids, husband and friends, it was a true exchange of culture and languages. I was amazed and super impression how she raised her kids (exactly what we in the Netherlands are trying to teach). 

We talked a lot about everything, played music together, inspired each other and they took me to the cutest monastery and nature area the next day.

Thank you so much for this authentic view of life in Ukraine and I hope to join you next year to try and teach children the value of life & nature.
Super nice guy, like to talk and share experiences. I hope you keep enjoying everything in your trip and hope back see you soon.

I am grateful to Alex ha that it took me to visit, and spent a lot of time with me. He showed me Kiev, different attractions and interesting places)
Alexey is a very kind person, and sociable, I recommend to come to Alexey. The house is quiet and peaceful, which allows you to have a good rest! Pleased to Meet You! And I wish many cheerful guests!

text: Even before Max and I met, we realized that we have a couple of mutual friends and so surfing with him was like staying with an old friend. He's very accommodating and you can definitely count on him on making sure that your stay in the city is comfortable and enjoyable. He's a great cook, generous and funny. He was very flexible even to my last minute schedule changes and even agreed to host a former host of mine from Istanbul who decided to visit Kiev very last minute. He cooked us delicious breakfasts and teas and hung out with us when he had time. We also shared a lot of interesting conversations on travel, relationships and life in general. I can definitely recommend him as a host and guest. Thanks so much for your hospitality Max. I really appreciate everything. I know we'll meet again, somewhere, sometime! Now you have more reasons to visit Canada. :)

Staying with Maksym was definitely the highlight of my brief stay in Kyiv. He is a lovely host, very warm and receptive: he cooked a bunch of times for us, showed me around and introduced me to all his friends - all very nice people; His flatmate, Abil, is a very cool guy too - we went to restaurants together and shared a lot of music.

It was a very good stay with you, Maks! I hope we do meet some day in the future and of course you're more than welcome anywhere in the world I end up living! (not just Brazil!)
Thanks! : )

Maksym was so wonderfully thoughtful during my stay in Kiev. I arrived while he was working and he let me leave my bag at his office right in the center of the city. In the mornings we shared coffee and breakfast and in the evening we shared dinners and stories. He was also hosting other surfers and we all had a great time together. He's a busy guy but he is enormously welcoming despite it. Thanks so much for your much appreciated hospitality!

Maksym was not just the best host ever, he was also an amazing friend who helped us with everything we needed. Since the begining the comunication was very smooth and friendly so when we were coming to his place we really had a feeling that we were coming to visit a friend of ours not just a host.
During our visit Max had to work so unfortunately he didn't have time during the day but that didn't matter because he always spent the evenings with us. There was another couchsurffer Weimin  accomodated at the time of our visit so we had a wonderful time meeting new people.
I was visiting Max with my friend and I had no idea that she secretly made a plan with him to make me a surprise birthday party.
We felt like we were at mum's place because Max offered us clean sheets and always woke up early to prepare breakfast. I can't express enough how welcomed we felt during our whole stay and I would like to say to Max that we are very grateful for the way he made us feel at his place. <3

He was my first host on couchsurfing. I was lucky to have such a great host. He gave us good infos about the city and show us around. He cooked meals, deserts for us and showed us his hospitalty. I hope to see him again.

Staying with Maksym requires a 3-page essay not a reference. His kindness and hospitality starts from the first time you sent the request and only gets better throughout the stay. He opened his sweet house, which is in great location with may attractions in walking distance, to us and made us feel as VIP guests. The house was super clean and he provided us with clean sheets. He is a great cook and he cooked for us several times during our 3 day stay. The words are not enough to express how grateful we are for this gentle soul. Although I enjoyed every bit of long conversations we had, I enjoyed the dark humors the most. It is not often that one comes across someone and clicks right away. I strongly recommend anyone who is looking for a true CS experience to host, be hosted by, or hang out with  him. You will have a lifetime memory and full of laughs. 

Thank you so much and hope we cross paths soon.

I can only use sweet and nice words to describe my stay with Maksym. He is witty, attentive, solicitous, kind of motherly protective and a great fun of cooking. There was always nice breakfast early in the morning and delicious dinners or very sweet chocolates from Belgium at night. 

Maksym is warm and very clever.  I wish him all the best and I may  see him soon -in Berlin or who knows where. 

Take care amigo and danke sch√∂n. Emilio

He is really hospitable person.  Also trustable and helpful person. He made everything for me and my friend what we need. He is organized person. ƒ∞f I come Kyiv again I would like to stay in his home.

I've stayed with Maksym 3 days during the week. Working days may be not the best choice, but it didn't change how great of a host was he.
Whenever he had time he showed me around and hang out. He's supper funny, open, accommodating and you can always count on his knowledge (maybe not about the historical dates though xD).
Also he's got super cool flatmate - Abil. If he's at your door, take him, if you're at his door, don't hesitate :D thanks again Maksym!

They also were uncomplicated, thankful and left my place tidy. I'd host them again and wish them a safe trip on their daring hitchhiking adventure!

If you're interested in learning about Ukrainian history and culture, you can not find a better host than Jeka! His passion for and depth of knowledge of Ukraine is almost hard to believe. We spent hours talking about everything from historical conflicts to the present moment to traditional music and the ways it has evolved and remained alive (especially since the most recent revolution). In our short stay, we even witnessed a rare performance of a significant musician/activist playing some of the most authentic tradition Ukrainian music one can ever hope to hear. His girlfriend is very sweet as well! Despite the pressure of school on her back, she agreed to host me and even prepared meals for Jeka and me while we spoke. I'm looking forward to the next opportunity I have to meet them again and learn even more about Ukraine and Kiev in particular. Thanks for everything!

There is really not much more to say than it is already written in references on his profile. His home is near one of the airports in Kyiv, a bit far from the center. If you don't mind using taxi, you don't have to worry. :)

:))

text:
Staying with Nicholas was such a huge pleasure! Both me and my friend Paulina greatly enjoyed surfing at his place - you really couldn't ask for a more relaxed, uncomplicated, easy-going and forthcoming host. His home in Kyiv is damn nice, cozy and super centrally located, just a couple of minutes walking-distance away from loads of interesting stuff. Nicholas also had a bunch of sights, bars and restaurants to recommend to us and took me on a great pub crawl Friday night, where we really had the chance to share stories and connect.
We really felt at home at your place, Nicholas - and both hope that this is just the beginning of our friendship! Thank you for everything and hope to see you soon again!

Nicholas was an excellent host for a weekend in Kyiv! It was great to explore the neighborhood and discover some of his favorite places. He has excellent taste in beer, cocktails, and food. Nicholas was a very hospitable and friendly host, and I would definitely stay with him again.
I really recommend Nicholas! Enough to say that I have new friend!!

Good man with a good soul! I'm glad we've met him on our journey.  It was really awesome to have opportunity to visit Kiev. Thanks for all your hospitality and advices and everything!
You're always welcome in Cracov!

Nicholas is knowledgeable, worldly and interesting local who made my stay in Kiev so much more awesome! Great guy to have a really fun and random day or night out with, very laid-back and flexible and much like the Ukrainian locals he definitely knows how to have a good time üòã

Nick was such a solid guy!  He was very accommodating and was ready to help/give advice whenever need be.  He has a superior taste when it comes to bars and restaurants: you‚Äôll never go hungry/thirsty if you stay with him :).  He is a master conversationalist and has a plethora of stories and topics to discuss about. Very clean home in a great location (his couch was also extremely comfortable).  He took me a out to a fantastic Georgian restaurant and introduced me to some of his wonderful friends which made for a great night!  Nick hosted me on the last leg of my journey and was very understanding that I wanted to just have a chill last few days (I was extremely grateful for this). He‚Äôs a very amiable, caring, fun dude.  Stay with him!

I had such a great time hanging out with Nicholas. Nicholas showed me and a fellow Couchsurfer his part of the city. I got to know some cool places, bars and restaurants since Nicholas took us on a little tour through old town Kyiv. I wish I could have spend one more weekend  with him and his friends to have a couple of beers, fancy cocktails and a few matches of ping-pong. Nicholas is a easy-going and fun guy to hang out with and he will give you a completely different perspective on the city and the country, since he used to live in several other parts of the world.
I hope to see you again some time Nicholas! If you are in the area of Frankfurt, just let me know ;)

My short stay at Nicholas place in Kiev was absolutely outstanding. Even though I had not much time to enjoy the city due to a short stopover during my onward journey, Nicholas really made my stay special. He introduced me the cocktail culture of Kiev and guided me to some really hidden as well as fantastic places. Moreover during our bar hopping we stopped by some touristic sights so that I was able to make the most out of my really short stay in Kiev. His apartment is clean and really charming. Hope to meet up again. I highly recommend him!!

Nicholas is a great guy! Really funny and kind. We spent some time together doing different activities from going to the gym to having one of the best burgers in the city. He allowed me to use everything in his house so I'm really greatful about that even knowing that I'm not a good cook hahaha.

Nicholas' profile picture is definitely a perfect representation, the only thing that might change is the background! At some point you'll definitely see him in a pub with a beer in hand.
Surfing with Nicholas was a great way to be introduced to fantastic Kiev; the first night, he showed me two of his regular hangouts, and we spoke about Ukraine, travel and of his love for Texas over great food and too many drinks. The second night, we checked out the Lavra and were lucky to have the entire Ukraine in WWII open air museum to ourselves.
It was great to hear the insight on Ukraine he's gained, see the enthusiasm he has for his new home as well as trade ridiculous travel stories. Recommend him to anyone visiting Kiev.
Awesome Host, great Appartment. Nicholas showed me around and showed me many cool secret Spots.. I found in nicholas a new friend..

I have heard a lot of stories about couchsurfing but how could I know it can be one of the best part of your trip! Of course this was because of Nick. He showed his true genuine part even from the first message.You may think its not possible to know someone in 3 days but there are some people you can understand even from first minute.He is been living in kyiv for 2 months but there are a lot of locals knowing him saying hi when we are passing by. He was already having a friend over just because his friends legs were really tall he gave him his bed and slept on sofa.And when me and my friend came he bought an air mattress,pillows,sheets for future couch surfers and slept with them while giving the sofa to us.He is an intelligent person who knows a lot and patient enough to explain them all.He showed us for 2 days and explained a lot about city even though he was there for a short time.10/10 would host him and stay with him again.See you in Bucharest or in Istanbul dude.Take care!

Nicholas is a great host! He met us up at the bus terminal, showed us local bars and took us to our first tailgate! We got to se the tallahassee local life. We had an awesome stay and got to meet a American metal band that was staying at nicholas as well. We had the best time and regret we couldn't stay longer.
This was our first couchsurfing experience. Nick made it great! He was an awesome host, and we all had a really good time staying with him. Thank you again, Nick!
I had a great stay at Nicholas place. Nick is a friendly guy who picked me up at the bus station and drove directly to the pub! I had an overall great experience as a surfer! Thanks man!

We stayed with Nicholas from Friday evening to Sunday morning. Nicholas was very pleasent an fun to be with. We went to a tailgating on Saturday with his friends, it was a lot of fun. Nicholas was also good at showing us Tallahassee and explaining about the rest of Florida and the states thats sorround the gulf coast. All and all a very pleasent host.

Nicholas was a great host; very friendly and helpful! We showed me around in the City and Extended my stay spontaneously when my car broke down... he even helped me to get to the mechanic and all that!! Thanks for that, i recommend this place 100%
Nicholas was so kind to host us. He has a cozy apartment. He found  time to show some part of the city and the bar. See you in Kazan! :))))))

text:
Nick was the first person I've couchsurfed with so I wasn't 100% what to expect. Couldn't have gotten a better guy.
Nick is very relaxed, hospitable, and easy to talk to. He's done his fair share of travelling resulting in a fair share of excellent tales. Tallahassee's resident bar mogul, he knows where to go every night, and seemingly all the staff.
We got along so well he ended up joining me on a spontaneous trip to southern Louisiana where we brought in the new year with our exceptional zydeco skills. He made an effort of showing me all he knew of Cajun culture and new Orleans (if you're ever there, get a drive through daquiri [daiquiri?], but hey, they don't put a straw in it). Additionally, he introduced me to the wacky world of college football. Go FSU!...wait.
Its not everyday you meet someone you can spontaneously spend the next week with 24/7. Top host and top guy.

I had an awesome time hanging out with Nick and his friends for the night.  It was great to chill out and talk while listening to his sweet record collection.  Thanks for the good beer and great company man! Let me know if you want to come out west.

Nicholas was a great host! Staying with him and meeting his friends was so joyful. 
Had a nice place on his couch and was so happy because of his great record collection.

I spend one really nice evening with Anton in a restaurant and at his place at Kiev. He is extremely knowledgeable and full of amazing stories. He is also a great chess and football enthusiast. A great pleasure to sum it up! Always welcome home at my place in Munich!
Couldn't ask for more!!! Had a great time during my very short visit in Kiev on they independence day.

Anton was very hospitable, and really did his best to make me feel at home :) We met in the centre - and he was so accommodating as my schedule was a bit hectic and I was quite late - and went straight back to his. We shared wine and dinner and talked late, comparing differences between Paris and Kyiv. I had lots of questions for him about Ukraine and he was really happy to talk about anything! He's a thoughtful guy, and was very sweet in giving me his own bed to sleep in and letting me borrow a towel and things like that. Sometimes conversation could be a little stilted because of our respective language barriers but he's very open and willing to chat. I had a good time with him!

Me and my girlfriend arranged an extremely last minute stay at Anton's for two nights. Due to a relatively complex series of events (we had one host that fell through, and a second host that could host us for the first of two nights who then got ill), our plans were very fluid. Anton, however, was completely gracious in first being able to host us for the second night but then also the first night at the last moment.

We first met with Anton after the Kyiv-Chelsea game (0-0, but a good game), which we both attended, albeit it separately. Afterwards Anton took us back to his flat, offered us drinks, and spent a good few hours hanging out with us and just chatting about stuff/life. He has a conceirge in his building, so he was able to leave his keys with us, which allowed us to lie-in beyond his earlier wake up time. We then met up in the evening again, had some beers, watched some more football (Real Madrid-PSG, 0-0, not that great a match) after which we spent some more time talking. 

Anton is a really interesting and friendly person, he was really easy to chat to, and I would not hesitate to recommend that people should stay with him! He has a super nice flat in fairly central location a short walk from a metro station. Me and my girlfriend shared a large sofa bed that was plenty big enough for the two of us which is sort of in the same room as Anton's bed but is sort of it's own room (it is one big room, but with a dividing wall in the middle that allows for privacy).

Thank you so much for hosting us Anton! All the best with everything, and perhaps we can meet up again sometime!
It was my first time to use Couchsurfing, but I totally loved it, he made my stay there incredibly awesome!! He is a really nice guy and I spent a great time there. Thank you Anton

He's a very open and nice guy who really loves walking. I'm happy he stayed a bit longer as I had some time to get to know him a little. I definitely suggest you to host him and of course I would host him again! Don't trust him when complaining about his English, he really speaks English he's just way too shy of it. text: Had a pleasure hosting Kyryl and his friend. I first met Kyryl at an even I hosted. We stayed in touch and next time he was in town he asked to surf at my place. I have met Kyryl and Denis outside of CS community as we were studying in same university in Kiev, Ukraine. That's why I was really excited when they requested to stay with me in NYC. Kyryl has always been a dear friend of mine, always thoughtful of others, always with smile on his face and easy-going. I see him and Denis as people who are sharing the best of Couchsurfing spirit, they are "professional guests":) Super clean, punctual and mindful of our space.
Kyryl is a great to walk around the city, because he takes lots of pictures depicting his and his host's journeys. Also, it was great to jam with him playing on whatever instruments we could find in the room and eat those well-forgotten Ukrainian chocolates that he brought from our Motherland.
I totally recommend Kyryl and Denis to all future hosts, don't miss the opportunity to meet them!

Kyryl is open minded, fun, creative guy. Also  flexible and helpful.  (I was delayed 1hour... Sorry). His stories of his profession, cultural studies and travelling are super awesome! Ihor hosted me for two days in Kiev and i couldnt wish for better host. He is sooo polite, kind and easy to get along with so i felt really cosy and comfortable. He helped me a lot during my first days of Ukrainian trip.

Ihor was an amazing host! I didn‚Äôt get into town till 1am and he stayed up to let me in. Not a lot of people would do that, which shows the kind of person he is. He was extremely helpful and taught me some current and past history about Ukraine. After work we he had time to meet me in the city have a few beers and talk about whatever while meeting other CS. He is the spirit of what CS is and the positivity that comes from meeting people all over the world. 

I know I‚Äôll meet up with him again someday cause I will be back to Ukraine. 

Thanks again Ihor for taking the time to host me.

Ihor hosted me and my husband in Cracow for two nights 27-29 January 2017.

As I knew Ihor from his previous stay with us in Rzesz√≥w, when I found out that now he lives in Cracow, I did not hesitate to contact him. After all these years he might have a slightly different physical look, but his friendliness and cordiality were exactly the same as I remembered. I highly appreciate that he and his girlfriend Marichka decided to host us, even if it could have been a discomfort for them to sleep altogether in one room. They served us really tasty breakfasts and we had some nice conversation. I hope it was not the last time we met, you are always welcome to Rzesz√≥w!

Ihor was a great host! He picked us up from the train-station, he knew a good pub in Krakow and we slept in his couch, while he was sleeping at the floor. I would definately recommend to stay at his place and to host him :-)
Igor humble and interesting person. And he prepares excellent peanut butter. Be sure to organize a photo shoot for you! Total you best.

Igor is a friendly and nice guy, who accepted my host request even though my profile was kind of empty. This is my first couch-surfing experience, and it was definitely positive. It was great to watch football together and have some evening talks with Igor, his friend and other two couch-surfers from Austria and Germany. Well, watching Ukraine-Germany match on Euro 2016 even sounds fun:) All in all, I am really thankful to Ihor, everything was great :)

Me and my friend stayed for two nights with Ihor in lwiw and it was great! He brang us to a Jewish restaurant , made awesome breakfast and the best; he had three bikes so that we could make a city tour by bike. Also we watched football together so all in all an amazing couchsurfing experience. I hope we will meet again :)

Ihor and his girlfriend, Marichka are truly wonderful people. Eager to talk and to spend time with their guest. I enjoyed every single moment with them, it was real pleasure! :) Thank you once again :)!

We stayed at Igor and his girlfriend for two days. They were very hospitable and told us a lot about life in Lviv and Ukraine. They fed us a delicious pizza and made tour of the city bars. We are waiting for you in Gomel, guys!

text: Anton and his friend were two nice students on a hitchhike through Europe. They made nudlesoup for the three of us :). Hope to see you again sometime.
Anton is a nice young guy, who is in love with traveling! He's got many stories to tell you and will make sure you won't get bored :)

Anton and his friend Oleg are really fun guests! We had a lot in common I think and I was especially happy to practice some Russian with them :) We hung out together in my apartment with some beers, food and good stories! 
They definitely have some good hitchhiking stories to tell since this is the way they travel. :) 
I wish you all the best in your travels!

Anton and his travel friend Alex stayed  at my home for a shrot time but we had interesting conversations on many topics. They are friendly, communicative and intelligent guys. In spite of the rainy day they had a nice walk in the city, joined Sofia free tour to know more about the history of the town. Anton and Alex really are well organized, clean, independent and good guests. Highly recommended! :) Hope to see you again!

Anton and Pasha came hitchhiking all the way from Kiev and we had so much fun skiing and snowboarding the whole day together, they were very organized and clean and I would definitely be a pleasure to host them again if they come to Brasov.
 I recommend them to everyone who wants to have fun and spend some good time as they are very energetic and open to adventures. 
Hope to see you in Ukraine guys!

text: I'm very glad that I got to this guy, very responsive and hospitable. Follow the order in the house. Knows a lot of steep dislocations in their city
Anton is very cheerful and a good guy! Hospitable and sociable. showed me his native city. I advise everyone to stay with this guy :)

Siergiej is really nice guy. He visit me with his friend for one night but it was nice. I feel confortable with them. Guys are funny and kind. Have a good way during your trip and take care. Kind regards. Mateusz
very positive guy, it was fun to stay with him and spend time with him!) thanks for spending the night and having a great time)

Charles is a vey nice and friendly gentleman. His apartment is awesome. Besides the good location, I have my personal bedroom and bathroom, plenty of spaces and I don't need to worry about the time to go and in. I felt like home. During my stay, he gave me a lot of advices and travel tips, he also showed me around the neighborhood, and took me to a restaurant where u can enjoy the full night view of Washington. I enjoyed so much the time we talked, ate, and walked around. Thanks so much Charles, 
Hope to see u one day in Hong Kong! ;)
Very nice guy and host ! I really enjoy staying at his place !

Charle(not Michael!) is a "easy"-going guy. His place is "good", you are completely independent, it's in the Chinatown and not far away from the touristic places.He is maybe often busy, but try to adjust his time with his guest, you have "no problem" to keep your own style, he will accept the way you are."That's it"!;) Thank you for the american food,drinks, bowling, and Italy wine. And to give me some american accent. Also thank you for interesting the culture of my country including accepting the hot water and my passion of tango also. lol. See you maybe one day in France or in China, or USA. who knows.

Charles is a friendly guy. A local from DC. He bought me dinner when I arrived and was working late the next night so I didn't even get to repay the favour. His place is pretty central, so easy to get to the sights.
Thank you for your kindness and letting me stay. I really enjoyed DC with you. I really love your place and Italian restaurant!! You are so great!!

Michael is a very nice person. Although I asked him to host me only one day in advance, he welcomed me in very nice room just for me with a queen couch. The area where he lives is also nice. Absolutely recommended.

Sasha and his girlfriend Sasha are really awesome couple. They offered me a good and comfortable bed. Staying there was a good experience for me. Sasha is extremely good musician and his gf Sasha is highly educated and responsive girl. She also made a tour for me to see Kiev. If you are looking for a good people with good vibes you should definitely visit them.

Lyuba stayed at my place one night,she is very cheerful and good girl.  Punctually arrived at the meeting place,shared his experience of traveling by hitchhiking.
Good luck)
Friendly, simple, quiet, funny and nice to have conversation about several topics. I enjoy her stay with me! Wish her the best!

Lyuba is just a sweet girl who is always smiling! She is always in a good mood.
Respectful and independent when it came to keeping herself busy.
I can recommend her as your guest if she ever happens to knock on your door. 
All the best to you dear Lyuba!**

My experience with Lyuba was very good. She is very kind and respectful. For sure I would host her again. I was very good to have some walks with her and to talk about many topics. She is very friendly and also a very interesting person.

It was a good experience hosting Lyuba for two nights. She were very pleasant guest, friendly and thoughtful. We had some nice meaningful conversations and good explorations around Fatima, including caves, castles, monastery and small villages. I can recommend others to host Lyuba.
Lyuba is a positive influence for those around her. She is innocent and strong at the same time. Wish you all the best!

Lyuba and her friend Irina were exploring Portugal, mostly hitchhiking ... And contacted me on the same morning, after their arranged host were impacted by the forest fire and he was forced to refuse them.

I was really nice to have Lyuba and Irina with us. We had good fun togheter!
On the last day they cooked a dish from Ukraine and we had an amazing dinner with good laughs!
Its very good to know young people that enjoy traveling  and know the other culture1
I was all the best to them and look forward to se them once again.

Lyubia is a kind, fun, respecful, smart and happy person. It was a pleasure to host and hang-out. I would definitively host again.  It was nice and fun to explore the east coast of my homeland. Wish to meet you again soon! You can trust her, and host her!
