If to talk about associations with luba  i have on my mind her kindness sincerity friendliness and cute feminity. She is clear open beautiful  mind, with hight potential to change the world toward better direction - what I do really  appreciate.
Be more persistence and it will lead you to new achievements 
P.s. greate thank to you for a letter it's inspirating. And wait for the letter  in  empty envelopment!
Sasha stayed for the weekend in my place. She is friendly, talkative and nice. Thanks for the cigarettes and booze :)

Sasha is a great girl. She is mature and she knows her responsibilities as a traveler. She likes to talk about her adventures while eating home made food. You can never get bored with her. I recommend this friendly human being to everyone. She will surely brighten up your day :)

I hosted Sasha for 2 nights. I regreted it. Never punctual. Late for dinner in both evenings. The second night it was my goodbye dinner I made with some friends of mine, cause the day after I finally left Bratislava for my summer vacation. I cooked for 8 people. 7 people waited for her half an hour before starting to eat and finally she came home when we already finished, without even texting/phoning me.
6 out of my 7 friends in the room were Csurfers, We were in the same room, joking, chatting, listening to music, singing, karaoking. It was possible to communicate in English, French, Italian, Spanish. She didn't take part/join/share anything at all. She was just playing with her tablet.
My friends are still asking why I took a person like that in my flat. But sometimes is good to make mistake. Now I know what I don't want. And I definitely don't want any longer this kind of sneaky traveller, who opportunistically use primarily Cs to save money, without any Cs spirit.

ps: really untidy and and dirty: I  found socks under her pillow.  2 times I cooked for her and 2 times she didn't even ask to help me tidying/washing. She took my stuff I always kindly offer to anyone, without even taking home something to share. UNBELIEVABLE.

text: Easy going, polite with a good sense of humour, I really enjoyed hosting Sasha. She was happy to share about her culture and her background and had a keen sense of curiosity for the local way of life. Extremely pleasant house guest too and most importantly, she loves tea like every cultured person should! ;)

Sasha 's a very nice girl , easy going and very friendly had a few conversations about life, politics in general , it's nice to hear her points of view about it as how I see it she just starting this long journey. She stay here four days and there will be a lot more to tell at her journey continue to other countries.

Sasha was very friendly, knowledgeable and amazing. I'd be happily agree to get hosted again :)

Sasha was such a helpful host and I really enjoyed my time staying in the fascinating city of Kiev! Her flat is in a great location, walking distance to all of Kiev's most interesting sights. Sasha herself is very knowledgeable about the city and has many interesting stories to tell. I learned so much from her! Point to any building in the city and she will be able to tell you some history behind it. She was my own personal tour guide :) Thank you Sasha for your kindness, for showing me some beautiful and harrowing spots and for helping me when I was feeling a bit ill. I will definitely come back to Kiev one day; I absolutely love this city!

Sasha hosted me and my two friends even though her profile said she could host 2. For that she gave us her room and prepared everything before we came to her place. We ate wonderful vareniky (dumplings) that her grandmother made and a delicious soup made by Sasha herself. She is very smart, intelligent and pleasant to talk to. She took us to a wonderful place for coffee and strudl where I left my soul :) The location is very good, when we stayed with her we almost did not use the public transportation, and the area where she lives is very vibrant and artistic. The apartment is amazing and warm. We hung out, talked and contemplated gender issues, politics, education etc.  Thank you for teaching us so much about Ukraine, the mentality and the political happenings and we hope the learning process was both-sided. Good luck in your educational project for the future, I am sure you will make the most out of it!

text: I hosted Roma and his GF Masha for 2 nights, they were nice, flexible and polite guests, Roma is a thoughtful and talkative personal, shared many interesting stories, had dinner together, went out for shisha and drink, I really enjoyed their stay in my house, and I highly recommend him for any host, hope to meet again my friend, wish you best of luck, thanks a lot for the biscuits, love it!!

Roman is one of thd must fun people that I met in Kiev!
We had really good time there and if I go to Kiev ever again I will send him a message for sure!
Thx Roman :)

Roman and his hospitality to us made me start rethinking the world we live in. He hosted us for three nights, went partying with us but also managed to share some valuable experiences and thoughts. I am almost sure this is not going to be my last trip to Ukraine and I hope we shall meet again. Host Roman and stay with him, he is cool!

Would I stay again??? üòÇüòÇüòÇ
OMG, of cource YES. Such talkative, friendly, educated, intelligent, easy going ppl as Roman make me hope that our world has chance :)
It was pleasure to stay with you, bro. So many common topics to discuss and so less time for it. Thanks a lot, and want meet you again!!!

Very smart guy, perfect english, extrovert, fun and helpful. Even though the time was quite short, we still got to share a few beers, stories, opinions and advces, so all in all it was a pretty cool day in Slovyansk.

We spend short but very good time at Roma's place. He was super helpful with some local contacts and very flexible as a host. We had great "about life" and photography talks his kitchen. And as his plan changed  it was very nice of him to organize a couch for us at his friends' place. Roma, you are very welcome to Berlin!

Roman is very intelligent, interesting and cheerful person. He and his girlfriend inscribed us, despite the fact that we were more than agreed from the beginning. Roma makes wonderful photos and can tell a lot of cool stories. We had a great time together and I'll be glad to meet them again.

If you need just one good reason to go to Sloviansk, that's meeting Roman and Maria !! 
They're an extremely friendly couple with a great sense of hospitality !
Roman is a brilliant guy who has a lot to say about his city of Donetsk, his country, life and the current situation in Donbass. You can spend hours talking about any topic (why should we stick to politics?) and have a cool exchange. 
And have a look at his photos !
Thanks Roman and Maria for the perfect evening at your place and the good food, I really enjoyed the moment ! And thanks for inviting me to that party last night, it was great fun !
All the best to you in the future, and keep it up !!!

I spend one really nice evening and night with Roman and his girlfriend at his place right in the centre of Sloviansk. He has a lot of really interesting things to tell about his job in the humanitarian sector and his own experiences in Donbas. He is also a great photographer and a good cook. Altogether I had a really nice time, and it would be lovely to meet again at some point!

Just a great host and person, which will make your stay in Slovyansk unforgettable and really comfortable.  I you have some thoughts, whether to write him or not, I can encourage you with these words of a famous thinker "JUST DO IT".

I hanged out with Roman and had a great time. He is very interesting and helpful young guy. We had a very interesting conversation all the time. We found that we have many common friends because he is working in Czech humanitarian organization PIN. I'm very impressed by his photography.

Ignat came with his friend and stayed for one night in my dormitory. They were hitchhiking to Warsaw from Kyiv and back. It was a bit last minute request, but fortunately one bed was free for them. They had cool stories and followed house rules. It was pleasure for me to give them a place to stay :) hope they got home safely! Good luck to you guys and see you!

I stayed for 2 nights and it was nice and positive time, especially Jackie Chan movies evening lol. Ignat is calm and hospitable person, I'm glad that I stayed with him.
Good luck with your trip to Poland as well!
Ignat hosted me 3 nights, he said about interesting and noteworthy plases in the town, gave me a bike for use to ride around the city. It was an excellent 3 days in Kyiv!

Super realiable, friendly and helpful

Surfing at Aras‚Äô place is much more than a couch and a roof over your head ‚Äî in Aras you will find a trusty Kurdish teacher, a well-read academic who claims he‚Äôs not one and doesn‚Äôt want to be üòä, an expert locator of a platter of delicious grilled meats, and an evening guide through the winding streets of the Old City of Mardin. 

After dinner, he took my friend and me to a rooftop caf√© with traditional Kurdish music and coffee ‚Äî definitely a highlight of our trip. Aras knows all of the good places to visit and eat in Mardin, and he also has a great taste in whiskey, chocolate, and comedy. :))) He is a sharp and worldly fellow, and I really enjoyed talking with him about culture, politics, travel, and language into the early hours of the morning. 

He and his housemate live in a clean and comfortable apartment, with a nice view from the balcony. Thanks for everything, Aras ‚Äî you‚Äôre always welcome as our guest in the Land of the Hittites. üòä

"let's go for a drink," after a knowledgable and historic conversation about some rrreal stories about Turkey history, Aras invited me to chill out around the old town Mardin, "I know some nice coffee there."

we went out and had a fantastic night. I was been introduced to one of his poet friend, and then talked about Ulysses and Japanese poems in a lovely bar. It was one of my favorite night when travelling in Turkey.

How does one describe Natalie!?

If you take an up-to-date encyclopedia of Kyiv, combine that with the energy of the Energizer Bunny (or is a cat?), put that in a human soul that treats you with genuine interest and care, and then multiply that by üíØ; you get someone that can probably come close to this gem of a person who kindly hosted me on my maiden CouchSurfing adventure.

Three days with her would feel like a lifetime (in a good way) and you'll return (or move onward) with a friend to cherish.

So would I recommend Natalie?

Well, if you are a host and lucky enough that you receive a request from her, I strongly encourage that you do not spare a moment least someone else shows the good judgement before you do and you miss on this incredible chance to meet her.

And if you are a surfer, make sure you take professional help to draft your couch request, get  a second review and they pray to the old gods and the new that she's not engaged in an adventure of her own.

There only are positive words that come to my mind when I think of Igor. I feel I am lucky to have won such a sincere friend. He is one of the most considerate and tolerant  human-beings I have met in my life (in 80-ish countries!). From the first moment I step in, I felt like I was taking with a close friend from before (which is not always the case for me when meeting new people) thanks to his hospitality and inexplicable warm character that naturally opens up people's heart. Despite his mild manner, I saw his enthusiasm, spirit of adventure, generosity, flexibility and iron tolerance to cope with all sort of diversity (culture, customs, religion, people's different character, values and behaviour)    he takes a great interest in his guests, people, their countries, cultures, religion, values and so on.

He takes great care of his guest, is boundlessly generous, practices "my home is your home" as he claims(not everyone can do at his level) and always makes sure that his guests are okay, at ease, feel home and happy. I can't find a word to thank him enough! 

He is very curious about other cultures and local food in other countries(it would be a great idea if you can cook/bring something from your country as I did although he never asks his guests) and enjoys conversations about everything, so if you are just looking for a free place in a fancy condominium in the city centre just to crush on without any communication, he might not be for you, but if you are keen to meet genuine Ukranean hospitality and warmth, go sending a request!

Without a second thought, I would recommend Igor to anyone to host/meet/stay with! Thank you also for the delicious breakfasts and fantastic free-ranged boiled eggs that you brought from your friends farm in the countryside, Igor! Thanks a million and see you again bro!;)
Ps. He is knowledgeable about Kiev where he has been living for 5 years, but he is also happy to share his knowledge of his home town Lviv!:)

text:
I host Alex 3 years ago in China. Now I come to Kiev. Alex also host me and show me the city. This is best part in Couchsurfing. This is the spirit of Couchsurfing. 
With Alex's help, I had a great time in Kiev. Travel like a local. I don't need to worry about anything, just followed Alex. 
Alex live in the edge of the city near to forest. There's a lake in the forest. It's a very interesting place full of fresh air. 
We also went to Russian style shower. It's one of the best activities in Ukraine.  I've never done that before. 
In a word, I highly recommend Alex to you. You can definitely trust him.

Vira and Alex are very friendly and respectful guests, it was a pleasure to host them. Vira is a good cook, she made a delicious ukrainian speciality one evening. I absolutely recommend to host Vira and Alex and wish you good look for your wourld tour :-).

Staying with Bohdan and his wife was a great experience! He took a lot of time to show me around the city and he told me a lot of information about the city and its interesting history. All the best to you both!!

Alyona and her friend Liza where amazing guests. They are both very smart, positive and well behaving girls. Olga was one of my most fun couchsurfing guests so far! She was to early at my flat (6am and not 7am) because she confused timezones and when I came home with other cs guests from the suicide circus club  in berlin at 6:50 we found her sleeping outside on a chair in my street. First we were not sure if it was her, but we asked anyways. So as everyone was tired because of traveling or clubbing all night we slept first a bit and then we checked out different places in Berlin including mainstream 
touristy things and some more authentic Berlin places. During our tour we got into sarcastic / ironic jokes about Ukraine, Germany and Berlin. I can confirm that Olga is indeed very talkative and witty, which is a lot of fun. Besides that she was one of my few guests that brought presents (Ukrainian vodka and chocolate - so pretty much everything you need in life). Later when my best czech friend (Tomas) arrived we made tons of crappy photos with various face expressions for a group chat to help her get some more hosts for her Europe trip from my European friends. 

After all we had such a great time that I decided to continue after my upcoming trip to Istanbul with Ukraine and I can't wait to meet her again.

text:
When I hosted Alexander in Ghent it was already decided he would return me the favour when coming to Buenos Aires, and what an awesome host he is! I had some good rest on his couch and I think Alexander is just really a lay back, fun guy to be around. He is again, welcome anytime where ever I live!

Oh but don't go up to his rooftop terras with pool, I promise you you will be soaked, if you want to or not. Hahaha

‚ù§‚úå

I really enjoyed my stay with Alex when I was in Buenos Aires. Even though it was only for 1 night we used the beautiful sunny day to stroll around the city, where he showed me around. Alex took me to many beautiful and interesting places like several parks and gardens and markets (ferias) that we're going all over everywhere due to the festive days; the very famous graveyard where he could teach me some more about Argentinian history and the famous people who were buried there. We also had some nice local food (Bondiolas) directly by the river in Puerto Madero, where people dance salsa and tango by the sunset. Too bad, that it was so freezing cold as soon as the sun had set..
In the evening we came back to his place to have dinner and watch a really eyeopening Movie which was so intense that we remained discussing, philosophing and having really deep conversations about the changes and effects of human impact on the world for almost the whole night. Not to forget about the combination with my first crazy mate-experience. This heavy Argentinian tea should definitely be denominated as a drug haha üòÖüôâ
The next morning we slept in until the early afternoon, but it was definitely worth it and after a quick but great Dip into the ice-cold pool on the rooftop of the building under the sun and fresh air on top of B.A., I was completely awake again and ready to cook some Breakkie (at almost 5pm :D :D ).

I am very thankful to have been hosted by Alex and which him all the best for his future!
And of course, whenever you‚Äôre going to be around Germany the next time, don‚Äôt forget to come and knock on my door :(even if its just to come in and eat up everything you can find in my kitchen haha :D)
Thanks for everything Alex!

un abrazo,
Teresa

text: Artem and Oksana are one of those couples who you meet and think "Yeah,that's how life is supposed to be lived". At least for me,that was the case anyway. text: We stayed with Artem and Oksana. They are very nice family with two sons. They are very hospitable to us. We went to the river with them and they showed to us fountains in the river.  To See the fountains was perfect. Thanks for everything‚ù£Ô∏è

I had a wonderful experience with this family!
Artem and Oksana are so adventurous and inspiring, even though we did not hang out much, I enjoyed the evening chats with them. I will always remember how delicious the "weird cheese" we had at the first evening, and the Ukrainian beer! 
I have so much to say but couldn't find a better word to describe how happy I was to stay with them. For me, the best experience here is not the attraction in Kiev but I had a chance to exchange the experience, to see the family value from others. Seeing Artem and Oksana playing with sons reminds me my childhood.
And I am honored to have the paper given by the older brother so I had a great time drawing with himüòÉüòÑ
Thank you so much for your hospitality, I will see you again next time! :)

My girlfriend and I had a wonderful time in Kiev and one of the main reasons were our hosts. Oksana and Artem are very friendly, hospitable, open to conversation, helpful and their 2 sons are adorable little fellows. They are everything that CS is about. I would highly recommend them to be a part of your journey in Ukraine or to host them.

It was a thought-provoking night meeting Artem and Oksana. The two of them are living inspirations in all aspects - a loving couple who respect each other, patient parents who listen to their kids' smallest requests, accomplished professionals in their own career fields and compassionate citizens who care about the future of Ukraine. They were knowledgeable enough to answer all my doubts about the historical background, current education system and political situation in Kyiv and Ukraine. 

Having Justin and Emilian around is definitely the icing on the cake. I witnessed with my own eyes that they have raised two confident and energetic boys. What a lovely night with this family :) Thanks for everything!

Artem is already a friend and now Oksana too. I am so thankful to them for letting me stay at their apartment even when they were not in town. After travelling to europe I was tired and it was so comfortable to stay at their place. I had a very comfortable stay. I wish to see them again. They even gave me birthday present. I wish them all the best . Cheers!!!

I was passing through Kiev on the way to Moscow and Artem and Oksana kindly invited me to visit them.  Unfortunately Oksana had been called away on business so I met Artem.
Artem is a very intelligent and charming guy.  I would have liked to have spent more time, but the hours we had were just perfect, he told me about Kiev and the Ukraine which I would not otherwise have known.  We went for an enjoyable walk in the neighborhood and had a delicious lunch (thanks Artem, IOU) 
I can  recommend anyone to meet Artem (and I am sure Oksana) 
Thank you both for your kindnesses
Bill

These guys are great!!! Put all the lovely words you can think of in a sentence and that basically sums up this family. I felt so welcome! There were loads of great chats and so many great stories. Artem and Oksana kindly hosted me for three nights in Kiev, Ukraine.

His place is located next to the river and easily accessible by bus and metro. The neighbourhood is quiet and nice, with many young couples living there.

Artem and I had a relaxing walk around his neighbourhood and I learnt a lot about Ukraine and its recent political affairs from him. He is knowledgeable and has a passion about writing. Artem and his family are very friendly and hospitable people. I, with my friend Pedro, spent really nice evening with them in Kyev, we are very grateful for your couch, thank you again! And enjoy Athens !! :)

Artemis and his wife are very friendly and knowledgeable, equipping a wide international view. They told much about Ukraine which I will never know from books or news. Its so glad to have them as host. Really want to meet them again and show them around hk!

My friend and I had such an enjoyable stay in Artem's home for two nights. He was a very generous host, and provided us with everything we needed and more. We had several long and interesting conversations about Ukrainian politics and global affairs. He shared many of his experiences working as a journalist in Ukraine and I learned so much from our time with him, and wish we could've stayed longer. We also loved spending time with his youngest son, and sharing meals together :) thank you for your hospitality and hope to see you in Sarajevo someday in the future!

Staying with Artem, Oksana, and their two cute little ones was the perfect Couchsurfing experience for me. They are both lovely, warm people; educated and interesting. Aside from giving me tips on places to go in Kiev, and how best to get there, we had a few long chats over tea or whisky on the politics of Ukraine and elsewhere, political philosophy in general, economics, journalism, and a host of other subjects. It was the best experience I could have hoped for, and made my trip to Ukraine particularly special :)

We stayed with Artem and Romawka for three wonderful night. They have two lovely kids and we hanged out all together as a family :). They kindly showed us the city center of Kiev and the Motherland Monument by telling the informative explanations. While kids were sleeping, we were having kitchen chats and enjoying. Their house is super relax and we did not feel ourself as a guest but a flatmate. I am sure that we will be meeting again and having another wonderful time in Turkey. Looking forward to host them.

text:
Jason could not host me at first, despite this we stayed in touch; he offered me tips and proposed to meet for a city tour and a daily excursion. I finally had the chance to stay at his apartment for one night, a clean and very well located place. 
We spent a good part of the night chatting, Jason being a very easy-going, fun-loving person. He is both an adventurer, a pioneer, with lots of great anecdotes and memories to share. Always with a touch of humour (or should I say humor?), he‚Äôll make your day brighter and for this among other things you should definitely meet him.

text: I have host Roman two nights. He was in Netherland for an congress and prefer to stay with locals. Roman is a very friendley person, honest, smiles a lot. But you can have fun with him. Absolute a person who I once hope to meet again. Roman, it was a pleasure to be your host and hope to meet you once again.

This is a neutral review. Roman behaved well, but failed to respect my sleeping time.

Roman left for Slush conference after-party after 9pm. We agreed that he be back by 01:30 in the night, so I will go downstairs and let him in. The after-party was about 30 minutes away by public transport. 01:10 he sends me a message asking if it's okay he'll come back by 02:00. I agreed on this. A little after 2am he sends me a message that he's now walking towards my place. 03:10 he arrives in front of my house.

His reason for being late was that he was helping a drunk (foreign?) girl get home. Now I'm not saying this isn't a valid reason. The biggest issue here is he failed to communicate his major delay to me. I didn't hear anything of Roman between ~2am and ~3am. I had to stay up to wait for him so I can let him in from the cold.

In any case, Roman behaved well during the day and we had nice conversations. But Roman, you must respect agreements or communicate your delays.
He is really nice man :) We had dinner and some nice talks. We also played a board game! I reccomend him as a guest, I would love to host him again!

Roman stayed at our flat in Wroclaw for one day. I was hosting my birthday party during his stay, so the place wasn‚Äôt really the calmest place on earth, but I hope he had a good time anyway. He‚Äôs a kind and polite person, really easygoing and fun to spend time with, I only wish I could spend more time with him, but who knows - maybe we‚Äôll have such opportunity in the future. Don‚Äôt hesitate and host Roman, you won‚Äôt regret it. See you in Lviv Roman!

I was visiting Kyiv for two nights and Roman hosted me during this time. That was a fantastic weekend. He is a very hospitable, kind and cool man, who told me a lot of advice and tips about the city. We talked a lot about music, IT sphere and shared our travel experiences. We spent an awesome time together hanging out! 
Really love Roman's hospitality and grateful to him for such great memories.
It was nice stay
Nazar is a nice guy. Shy and quiet. It takes effort to get him to talk but he is very respectful and easy going.

Nazar and Sasha are a nice couple to host. Friendly, clean and punctual. When you are not used to speaking English on a daily basis it can be difficult to start communication. But I think you are making good progress. You will get more talkative soon. Thanks for choosing me as host. Welcome back any time, Nazar and Sasha.

Nazar and Sasha are very kind people. Unfortunately, due to some last minute changes from my side, we could spend very little time together, so I didn't had any time at all to get to know them a bit better. 
Nazar, if you ever pass through Antwerp again, let me know, and I'll make it up to you.

Nazar and Sasha were shy, polite and clean. They stayed for a night had kept me updated about their trip and plan almost 2 months ago. 

I would like to suggest you both to try and interact with host you meet. I was looking forward to talking to you both but despite my several efforts to initiate a conversation you, you guys continued to chat with each other in Ukrainian. I tried my best to cook for you with fractured hand because I enjoy introducing my surfers with my cuisine because CS is all about sharing food, music, ideas, stories and obviously place to sleep. The people you meet in your journey you might never see them again, it's nice to make new conversations too sometimes.

I wish you both a great journey and adventure wherever you go. All the best.

Namaste :)
Me and my housemates spent a few evening chatting with Nazar. Being shy, Nazar was politely navigating our political questions about Ukraine. He was a very quiet and easy to host guest.

text:
After feeling slightly lost on my first day in Kiev - the masses celebrating the national holiday (party crowds, political demonstration, Miss Ukraine!) - it was a blessing to arrive at Lena's and Vadim's place. Not only the warm welcome, but also the warm soup and cozy couch made it straight into my heart. After learning about their lives, jobs and jokes I felt I really wanna be friends with this cool and gorgeous couple. 
I'm much in love with their creativity: Vadim's photos are the top of the top when it comes to capturing emotions, moments and (not always so) random situations. Lena becomes a true artist when she "paints" lids, lips and eyebrows. Lena, you made my secret girl's dream come true by transforming me into Cinderella, a once-in-a-lifetime feeling never to be forgotten. Let's keep in touch by all means and thank you, thank you, thank you!!

text: it was great to have rina as i guest, she cooked nice meals and made her stay a pleasure. unfortunately i couldnt show her the city but im glad she liked it and i hope she will come back one day

Rina and her housemates were so incredibly nice. Especially as we had had a stressful time getting through the Ukrainian/Polish border crossing which meant we arrived at the house a lot later than expected. Which Rina was fine about, she even made us a little bit of dinner,as again we hadn't eaten properly due to the crossing. All of her housemates were lovely and we had a great time talking to them all. My husband and I slept in a single bed, which was cosy enough for the two of us.  
We all left in the morning together to take the local bus into town which was a very short journey away. We would recommend Rina to anyone. 
Thank you so much Rina and the gang, for being such amazing hosts.
fromPublicAddressDescription: Stoke-on-Trent, England, United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland

text: Actually we did not stay at Rina's, though she accepted our request. Our plans changed. But she seems a very nice and friendly person. She is reliable and she answers very fast so the communication was very clear. Thank you, Rina. Hope to meet you next time :) All the best.

Kolia is a friendly and open-minded person. It was cool spending time with him, he's a traveler and has many things to share! The house he lives in is spacious, clean and cozy and the family is very hospitable. He also got me on a good hitchhiking spot on his car and gave some sandwiches :D
Feel free contacting with him, you won't regret ;)

Kolia has the most hospitable family we ever met. They have given us a lovely, separate house, where we had everything you could dream of. Moreover they created the perfect conditions for a great stay-a nice place, amazing food, and great company. We enjoyed our time together, especially in the evenings, while watching movies or talking. Indeed, Kolia has wonderful experiences to share, and some interesting ideas. He and his whole family (including some cute dogs :) ) were extremely nice, and we would definitely want to hang out once more!
Niv hosted me for one night and it was enough to say how he‚Äôs a welcoming and kind person. We had some tea and a nice conversation. Thank you!
I came to Kolya in Kyiv to discuss our trip in Norway. He is very hospitable and interesting host, we talked a lot about travel. I recommend him, see you soon:)

Yevhen... Yheven is one of the nicest people I've ever met!
He is just such a people person that you can feel confortable around him very very fast. He is funny, respectful, open minded and lovely! :)  It was a great experience to host him!

Yevhen is an intelligent and easy-going guy full of stories about his travels and life in ukraine. Good to hang out with and have a conversation - see you again somewhere in this world!

text: Zhenia, along with Pasha, Masha and Roma, were amazingly kind and open and made me feel at home right from the outset. On the first night we were also joined by Daniel, Oksana and Sofia, with whom we drank tequila and went a little way to putting the world to rights. I arrived wearied from a busy departure from Kharkiv, but the energy and enthusiasm I saw in Zhenia's sunny 6th-floor flat buoyed me through my first few days in Kyiv.

Kiev was remarkable thanks to him and his great friends(which are now also my friends). Friendly atmosphere, great conversations and hopefully start of a lifetime friendship :) already missed them and their kindness. One of a kind in Ukraine :) It'd be a big loss if you miss a chance to host/surf him! :)

I arrived at Veronika‚Äôs quite late in the evening, and after trying to find her home with a dead-battery mobile phone (haha), I was finally helped by a local who rang Veronika and she came to meet me with a smile on her face. Upon arriving at her home, she immediately offered to wash all of my clothes without me even asking, which was lovely of her, and we then ate some food and talked for a while about Ukraine and other things and it was nice to hear her opinions about things. 

Veronika has a beautiful home and one which I had pretty much all to myself for 6 days whilst she worked; however, we did find the time to explore some beautiful places in Kiev and it was nice to hangout with Veronika and get to know her. I also had the pleasure of walking her cool dog ‚ÄúHunter‚Äù and we became best friends very quickly haha! He is supercool and you will all love him as much as Veronika does. 

Veronika is a very smart, strong, independent, very nice and polite person (and great host) who I recommend you meet/surf/host with and it was great to stay in her home in the more local part of Kiev to see the real, local life. I would not hesitate to recommend you surf at Veronika‚Äôs. Thanks again, Veronika. Until next time...

Veronika is a good woman and I thank you very much. I would definitely recommend her. She is a very understanding and helpful person. I appreciate her, she is very polite and kind. She likes to conversation, she is knowledgeable and also open-minded. I am very pleased to meet you. 

Best wishes, Cheers!

text: Orest is such a good person who anybody can trust and host. Unlike an ordinary traveller, he's like a friend who you've already known before. While hosting Orest, ask him for whatever he may want, or he won't ask for anyting for not to disturb you. I wish to see him again.
Orest has really good character. He met with my friends. We traveled together sometimes. Everything is okey for him. I absolutely would host him again.
Orest is friendly and respectful.More mature than your age.It is a beautiful experience to get to know the orest together for 2 days ..Maybe we can even go to see the orest again.

Viktoria was very friendly and kind. We spent 3 days together and I can say she was like the perfect guest for me and my friends who live with me. Hope to see her soon.

I hosted Viktoria and her friend Iryna for some days and we had a great time with my roommates. We played, they cooked a Ukrainian dish, I showed them around the city, they taught me about their country, culture and brought amazing gifts from there. They are very lovely guests. Hosting Viktoria and Iryna was a pleasure for me and I would do it again. I wish you all the best.

Viktoria is really a social, intellectual, and really easygoing person. She has fantastic experience of living in different countries, and she has a lot of interesting stories to tell. We cooked together and we had a lot of fun!!

Viktorya and her friend Iryna stayed at my place for four days and it was very very nice. They are lovely, thoughtful and friendly persons, we played, had dinner (I tasted an authentic Ukraine dish called Borshch) and made a tour in the city. I learned many things about their country and I liked so much the gifts they brought us. We had a great time together, I really appreciated them company.
Come back when you want, you're welcome anytime. Hope to see you soon.

I would like to thank much Aliona by the couch. and not only the couch..because Aliona is someone who helps travelers offering them not only her personal space but because she is an All-in-one person... A personal tourist guide. She helped me washing my clothes along with hers and she offered me coffee in the morning. She makes you feel at home. Thank you for taking care of me when I had cold fetching the medicine, for inviting me to her interesiting traveller's meetings and acepting me to meet her close group of friends. 
Thanks Aliona for the long conversations about all different kind of topics. Certainly Aliona is a 
exceptional girl ,very smart!! (Although some times too busy because of many activities she has!.) She represents the model of what a perfect couchsurfer should be and even more. I hope that some day I will have the chance to reward so much attention.

I stayed on Alionas very comfortable couch for a whole month, which allowed me to have a very interesting internship and I think that describes her generosity better than I ever could. I got to know her as a very smart passionate language teacher, who manages her tight schedule and her athletic aims no matter how depressing the weather in Kyiv can be.
One of the things I like most about her is how frank she is. I could never imagine her to be involved in a misunderstanding at all. 
Although something always got in the way, whenever we wanted to have a tour together, her advice and commentary really shaped my experience of the city. I felt a bit like one of her students myself, whenever I came home from sightseeing, told her where I have been and she answered something like: "Oh, that's nice. Did you know, that ..."
I also spent some time with her friends and students and enjoyed learning Dixit with them.
So in short: Aliona is a great person and I wish I could offer her a couch at a place that is more sunny than Berlin.
I hope we will meet again and maybe even at the Bulgakov Museum.

I have spent one very nice evening at Aliona‚Äôs place. Her couch was very cosy which made me feel at home. Aliona accept my request even she had very busy schedule. She waited me under snowy weather for several minutes and she even dont complain about that. We went to shopping together and she let me try some local food. She is quite talkative and social person which you will love to listen. Aliona gave me useful advices about where to visit in Kiev and also Lviv. She helped me to buy my night train ticket to Lviv which is one of the best way to travel through Lviv. I am so happy to meet her and I would definitely love to stay with her or host her at Istanbul. Lastly I wish my best for your forthcoming swimming tournament and hope to keep in touch:)

Aliona is an awesome person! 
(Host me for 4 days) 
She told me an amazing stories. And showed up some hidden stories of buildings. 
I wish you to realize your travel plan!
And I recommend everybody to host/stay with Aliona as trusted member!

My wife and I stayed with Roman 2 nights. We had a beers and conversations. Roman told us about the city and tried to show something besides our deals (very nice). But most exited was conversation about Physics, in which Roman is very strong. I was interested about low level, about atoms and photons and electricity. And I've got a lot of knowledges. Roma thank you for your hospitality and your knowledges that you shared with me! You're welcome in Belarus! :)

Roman a very intelligent person.
I recommend

We are very grateful to Roman for having hosted us! Sadly we only stayed for one night as we were leaving the next day, but I really hope we can meet again some day and share more :) Thank you very much, we felt very welcomed. If you ever visit Spain one day please contact me, you're super welcome :)
Have a good Christmas!!

text:
Karina and her boyfriend stayed for 1 night. It was a good and fun night. We had some drinks and talked about everything.
They are great couple.
Hope to meet you in Ukraine because I have to try some of the meals you cook and train with you :)

What can I say about Karina and Alex I really don‚Äôt know. They are wonderful couple and I am too lucky to meet and stay with them. I stay with them 2 nights and in the first night my flight‚Äôs arrival date was 3 am and they accepted me to their home that much late and order taxi for me from airport to their home. Second night, I wanted to go out and they were ok to come too late home and didn‚Äôt make any problems. On Sunday we went with their friends to Dnipro River to do SUP. It was my first experience and they taught me how to do it and we enjoy all together. After that, we walked around city and went to Gastro restaurant to eat and smoke hookah.

I really enjoy with that awesome couple and I totally recommend to everyone to stay with them or host them. I am totally sure you will not get bored with them. Don‚Äôt miss the chance to meet with these wonderful people!

Guys, see you in Istanbul and I promise you will have same hospitality!

text: It was great staying with Sasha, he helped me so much during my stay both in Kyiv and in Lviv! I first contacted him for information a few months ago and he gave me advice and followed up with me about my plans.  First he offered to host me in Kyiv, then I ended up staying with him in Lviv as well, and go on a road trip with him and his friends back from Lviv to Kyiv. It was great to meet his parents and his mom is such a sweetheart!   She made a delicious Ukrainian breakfast,  helped me practice my Russian, and helped me to buy a Vyshivanka from the local market.  In Kyiv, Sasha helped me find my way around while he was working, and also invited me along to some clubs with his friends.  Thanks for everything, Sasha, I had a really good experience in Ukraine, and I really appreciate all your help!  Safe travels to you in Central America, I hope you remember the Spanish phrases I taught you  :-)  Let's keep in touch, and you're always welcome to come visit me here in San Diego.  Dobre dyakuyu!!!

text:
My girlfriend and I stayed with Zlata over the weekend of the champions league final. They saw the difficulty for fans trying to organise accommodation here and very kindly offered to let us stay. 
The apartment was very spacious and clean. We even had our own room! 
Zlata, her boyfriend and her family prepared lunch for us and helped us with any questions or recommendations we needed.

text:
Dragan was "the last but not the least" (as the expression goes) guest of mine in Kiev, Ukraine „ÉÑ

He actually didn't directly CouchRequest me, but Vera with who I was sharing my life & (her) apartment. We decided to host him even though I was living my last days there, and I am happy I took this decision.

Such a funny guy, always joking... even though he sometimes doesn't get when YOU are joking... anyway, that created even more fun situations ;-)

As well the salad he prepared was really good. And I appreciated that he offered to go to buy groceries & actually did so... even though it was far for him ;-D

And definitely easy-going (for instance he asked us for 2 days, I offered him 1 day & he was OK with it... when so many people in this case prefer their comfort, he chose to privilege getting the chance to get new friends).

He was my first guest ever from the Balkans, and I am definitely willing to get the chance to know more people like him!

Good luck in everything my friend „ÉÑ
